text: I am Addison DeWitt.I'm nobody's fool, least of all yours.

text: -I never intended you to be.-Yes, you did, and you still do.

text: Not with me, you're no champion.You're stepping up.

text: Please say what you have to say,plainly and distinctly,
title: All About Eve

text: and then let me take my nap.
title: All About Eve

text: Very well. Although it's unnecessary,because you know what I'm going to say.
title: All About Eve

text: Lloyd may leave Karen,but he will not leave Karen for you.
title: All About Eve

text: -What do you mean by that?-More plainly and more distinctly?

text: I have not come to New Havento see the play, discuss your dreams,

text: or pull the ivy from the walls of Yale.
title: All About Eve

text: I came to tell you that you willnot marry Lloyd, or anyone else,

text: because I will not permit it.

text: -What have you got to do with it?-Everything.

text: Because after tonightyou will belong to me.

text: Belong? To you?

text: A dull cliché.

text: "Belong" to you?

text: That sounds medieval.Something out of an old melodrama.

title: All About Eve

text: "That you and I...?"

text: Now remember, as long as you live,never to laugh at me.

text: -Get out.-You're too short for that gesture.

text: Don't pick up that phone.Don't even touch it.

text: When that alarm goes off,go to your battle stations.

text: What of it?
title: All About Eve

text: True, your parents were poor,and still are.

text: They would like to know how you are.

text: What of it?
title: All About Eve

text: A matter of opinion, granted.

text: It's also true you worked in a brewery.

text: But life there was not as dullas you pictured it.

text: -She never proved a thing!-But the $500 you got to get out of town

text: She was a liar. She was a liar!

text: There was no Eddie, no pilot.You've never been married.

text: and the women who loved them.

text: -You repaid her by trying to win Bill.-That's not true!

text: I was there. I saw you and heard youthrough the dressing-room door.

text: -You lied to me about it.-No!

text: I had lunch with Karennot three hours ago.

text: Please, please.

text: But that in itself is probably the reason.

text: You're an improbable person, Eve,and so am I. We have that in common.

text: Also a contempt for humanity,an inability to love and be loved.
title: All About Eve

text: Insatiable ambition and talent.
title: All About Eve

text: We deserve each other.Are you listening to me?

text: -Then say so.-Yes, Addison.

text: And you realize and you agreehow completely you belong to me?
title: All About Eve

text: Yes, Addison.
title: All About Eve

text: Then take your nap,and good luck for tonight.

text: I won't play tonight.
title: All About Eve

text: I couldn't. Not possibly. I couldn't go on.

title: All About Eve

text: (door closes)

text: (Addison) And she gavethe performance of her life.
title: All About Eve

text: And it was a night to remember,that night.
title: All About Eve

text: (applause and cheering)

text: Honored members ofthe Sarah Siddons Society,
title: All About Eve

text: distinguished guests,ladies and gentlemen.

text: What is there for me to say?
title: All About Eve

text: Everything wise and wittyhas long since been said

text: by minds more matureand talents far greater than mine.

text: For me to thank you as equalswould be presumptuous.

text: I am an apprentice in the theatre,
title: All About Eve

text: and have much to learn from all of you.
title: All About Eve

text: Let me say only that I am proud and happy,
title: All About Eve

text: and that I regard this great honor
title: All About Eve

text: not so much as an awardfor what I have achieved,
title: All About Eve

text: but as a standard to hold againstwhat I have yet to accomplish.
title: All About Eve

text: (applause)

text: And, further, that I regard itas bestowed upon me only in part.
title: All About Eve

text: The larger share belongsto my friends in the theatre,
title: All About Eve

text: and to the theatre itself
title: All About Eve

text: which has given me all I have.
title: All About Eve

text: In good conscience,I must give credit where credit is due.
title: All About Eve

text: To Max Fabian. Dear Max.
title: All About Eve

text: who took a chance onan unknown, untried amateur.

text: To my first friend in the theatre,
title: All About Eve

text: whose kindness and graciousnessI shall never forget,
title: All About Eve

text: Karen. Mrs. Lloyd Richards.
title: All About Eve

text: It was Karen who first brought meto one whom I'd always idolized,
title: All About Eve

text: one who becamemy benefactress and champion.
title: All About Eve

text: A great actress and a great woman,
title: All About Eve

text: Margo Channing.
title: All About Eve

text: (cheering)
title: All About Eve

text: To my director,
title: All About Eve

text: who demanded always a little morethan my talent could provide,
title: All About Eve

text: but who taught me patiently and well,
title: All About Eve

text: Bill Sampson.
title: All About Eve

text: (applause)
title: All About Eve

text: And one without whosegreat play and faith in me,
title: All About Eve

text: this night could never have been.
title: All About Eve

text: How can I repay Lloyd Richards?
title: All About Eve

text: (applause)
title: All About Eve

text: How can I repay the many others,
title: All About Eve

text: so many,I couldn't possibly name them all,
title: All About Eve

text: whose help, guidance, and advice
title: All About Eve

text: have made this, the happiestnight of my life, possible.
title: All About Eve

text: Although I am going to Hollywoodnext week to make a film,
title: All About Eve

text: do not think for a momentthat I am leaving you.
title: All About Eve

text: How could I?
title: All About Eve

text: My heart is here in the theatre,
title: All About Eve

text: and 3,000 miles are too farto be away from one's heart.
title: All About Eve

text: I'll be back to claim it, and soon.
title: All About Eve

text: That is, if you want me back.
title: All About Eve

text: Good night to you all,and to all, a good night.
title: All About Eve

text: For services rendered beyondwhatever it is of duty, darling.
title: All About Eve

text: Come on, I'm the host. I got to get homebefore my guests start stealing the liquor.
title: All About Eve

text: -Congratulations, Eve.-Thank you, Karen.
title: All About Eve

text: -Congratulations, Miss Harrington.-Oh, thank you so much.
title: All About Eve

text: Nice speech, Eve. But I wouldn't worrytoo much about your heart.
title: All About Eve

text: You can always put that awardwhere your heart ought to be.
title: All About Eve

text: I don't suppose there's a drink left?
title: All About Eve

text: -You can have one at Max's.-I don't think I'm going.
title: All About Eve

text: -Why not?-Because I don't want to.
title: All About Eve

text: -I'm so happy for you, Eve.-Thank you so much.

text: Max has gone to a lot of trouble.
title: All About Eve

text: This is going to be an elaborate partyand it's for you.
title: All About Eve

text: No, it isn't. It's for this.
title: All About Eve

text: -It's the same thing, isn't it?-Exactly.
title: All About Eve

text: Here, take it to the party instead of me.
title: All About Eve

text: You're being very childish.
title: All About Eve

text: -I'm tired. I want to go home.-Very well. I'll drop you off.
title: All About Eve

text: I shall go to the party alone.I have no intention of missing it.
title: All About Eve

text: -Who are you?-Miss Harrington.
title: All About Eve

text: -What are you doing here?-I... I guess I fell asleep.

text: Please don't have me arrested.I didn't steal anything. You can search me.
title: All About Eve

title: All About Eve

text: I sneaked in and hid till she'd finished.Then I just looked around.
title: All About Eve

text: I was afraid someone would noticethe lights were on, so I turned them off.
title: All About Eve

text: -Then I guess I fell asleep.-You were just looking around?
title: All About Eve

text: -That's all.-What for?
title: All About Eve

text: -You probably won't believe me.-Probably not.
title: All About Eve

text: -It was for my report.-What report? To whom?
title: All About Eve

text: About how you live,what kind of clothes you wear,
title: All About Eve

text: what kind of perfumeand books, things like that.
title: All About Eve

text: You know the Eve Harrington Club thatthey have in most girls' high schools?
title: All About Eve

text: -I've heard of them.-Ours was one of the first, Erasmus Hall.

text: -I'm the president.-Erasmus Hall. That's in Brooklyn, isn't it?
title: All About Eve

text: You're going to Hollywood, aren't you?

text: Mm-hm.

text: I might.
title: All About Eve

text: That spilled drink's gonna ruin your carpet.

text: Maid'll fix it in the morning.
title: All About Eve

text: -I'll just clean up the mess.-Don't bother.

text: -How'd you get up here from Brooklyn?-Subway.

title: All About Eve

text: With changing and everything,a little over an hour.

text: It's after one now.You won't get home till all hours.

text: (buzzer)
title: All About Eve

title: All About Eve

text: You rest. I'll get it.
title: All About Eve

text: Hello. Who are you?
title: All About Eve

text: Miss Harrington's resting, Mr. DeWitt.She asked me to see who it is.
title: All About Eve

text: Well, we won't disturb her rest.

text: It seems Miss Harrington left her awardin the taxi cab. Will you give it to her?

title: All About Eve

text: It's a very famous name, Mr. DeWitt.

text: -Phoebe?-I call myself Phoebe.
